headline: US Stock Market Today S&P 500 Futures Edge Higher As Chip Demand Strengthens
summary: The Morning Bull - US Market Morning Update Monday, Feb, 9 2026 US stock futures are slightly higher this morning, with E-mini S&P 500 contracts up about 0.1%, as investors react to a mix of stronger global trade and cautious bond markets. Taiwan’s exports jumped 69.9% year on year in January to a record US$65.77b, with sales to the US more than doubling, which points to solid demand for chips and electronics that feed into many US technology and industrial supply chains.
